"I ordered the deep dish pizza from BJ’s in Laurel and it was very hearty and filling. The crust was thick and buttery with a nice golden bake, holding up well under all the toppings. The pizza was loaded—pepperoni, sausage, and ham were generous, so you definitely get your money’s worth if you like a meat-heavy slice.\n\nFlavor-wise, it was savory and rich, but on the greasier side, which is pretty expected with deep dish. The cheese was melty and abundant, though I would’ve loved a bit more balance with the sauce—it could’ve used a touch more seasoning or tang to cut through the richness.\n\nOverall, it’s a solid deep dish option when you’re craving something heavy and indulgent. Not an everyday pizza, but perfect for sharing or when you want comfort food that really sticks. ***Mondays Large Pizza is $20"",""Images"":[""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2dDy948v8oRIHMNv_613U5wK94di_52gySqFbbuHss2HvfrznX1xqhgaIIbMzNxke7vIta_0M8fvWhpyQhRT_PHm732tepd4iH8v27Ev6V2nvFojF6wSBZFrEURVhNfAR6ofvdRmX5fZs=k-no""],""When"":""2025-12-16""},{""Name"":""Nina Smith"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPvA_43X6ukNXZIIPa5cyAVnETsinrQjU2WLKXOeqgwgRdgo9k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100"",""Rating"":5,""Description"":""Hands down, great food and great service! The food was hot and fresh, you could tell it hadn’t been sitting under a heat lamp. It came out as soon as it was ready, and the presentation was on point. Huge shoutout to our server Juan, he was super welcoming and friendly. And can we talk about his AMAZING sweet tea?! I’d come back just for that alone! Overall, 10/10 for both service and food. We will definitely be back!"",""Images"":[""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1BBCrozfO_W0zV9kmgHLK5eaCgq41ST0EzUg27aOJoOSM8LOg8ajpnhONClr9fZu-yd6J6Zbe-nI74jD-Wfc3ZQ5ipeQd_NEyA54UlRjieGI0a0THDtKUVGNgAGJMCvXnDyCFq=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0Eo02b1WvRo2CdAWAxQALIHqYwtuDnACJM_CpRFemLrK4kS_q6FB6T3EavKgB9VR-4A