""When"":""2024-12-15""},{""Name"":""Voncia"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVM0EE9sUC4UnFxveSPiKO3ZxxpJMlXfnYxBYPcCYo_IQt_zZM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100"",""Rating"":3,""Description"":""Stick to Pot Pies, Skip the \""Empanadas\""\n\nI really wanted to love Restaurant 198, especially since finding a place with a variety of meatless empanadas is usually a win for a vegetarian. Unfortunately, the \""excitement\"" I felt upon arrival died a very slow death.\n\nThe Service: Non-Existent\n\nIt took 15 minutes just to be acknowledged. When someone finally approached me, it wasn’t \""Table for one?\"" or \""Dine in?\"" but a cold \""How can I help you?\"" as if I were lost. Once seated, the neglect continued. I had to flag the waiter down just to tell him my food was cold and to ask for the bill.\n\n* Greeting: 0/10\n* Customer Service: 0/10\n\nThe Food: A Culinary Identity Crisis\nWhen the plate finally arrived, the fries were stone cold. But the real heartbreak was the empanadas:\n\n* The Crust: If you like authentic empanadas, look elsewhere. This was essentially a pot pie crust. It lacked the proper texture and fry of a real empanada.\n\n* The Fillings: I tried the Shrimp and the Bean \u0026 Corn. Neither could save the dish. Between the presentation and the lack of flavor, \""disappointed\"" isn't a strong enough word.\n\nFinal Verdict\nIf you’re looking for a pot pie disguised as Latin street food and service that makes you feel invisible, this is the spot for you.\n\nFor everyone else who knows what an authentic empanada should taste like: avoid the madness and go somewhere else.\n\nFood: 0/10"",""Images"":null,""When"":""""},{""Name"":""Ekaterina Strigina"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjpnH-vuCvveNaDNN8hxpvorQI8sdM_Q5iShkMC_16KrLofLo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100"",""Rating"":3,""Description"":""It is a good place to have breakfast. They have a classic breakfast named after their restaurant. I got an omelette with veggies and asked for mushrooms as an add-on.\nThey add coffee if you finish yours, but it wasn't very hot (but I really need boiling temp, so it is for you to decide).\nThey customized my omelette by adding mushrooms to it. The amount of cheese was decent, and I'm glad they did not add salt to eggs because it tasted just right with the cheese! Loved it. They serve salad (just greens - nothing else) with the omelette, but there was not enough dressing in my opinion.\nThe total bill for two whether coffee and orange juice was $40."",""Images"":[""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn15TAEXc46orT1770fv8uC23K-HWpsG5V5bVJv1zptmsi5aDYsPxpTs1BrkK5t3v6hKlsMJ-J897epQyCzcVmK5eao-3cS5lEi51yreKR0NvGTpjuejvC11qOUV6W3N-o2wTBz3r9VoHTEz=k-no""],""When"":""2025-7-19""},{""Name"":""Dennis Williams Jr"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVFbMrEnb4Dq0_OFPBLO-_IfSAkUoxN5nDn2m8LG3l9MbxdAsgSg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100"",""Rating"":4,""Description"":""This is a nice place. Locally owned from what I understand. I had the chilaquiles with the green sauce and it was great! I’d get again and again. The waffle was a little underwhelming, I’ll give that a 3.5/5 meaning slightly above average. I got it because I saw someone else with the apple pie waffle and it looked amazing. The apples were more red delicious than Granny Smith and I need that tart/sweet. My son got the cinnamon toast French toast and it was delicious.\n\nI recommend trying this place and I will again when I visit next. The pancakes 🥞 looked good!"",""Images"":[""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1g1yoqADTeqYUxmoW1ht266uN_zUWIrG7XJ8hB8ZtsEwKmOGDZqARz2m-DQ0gvGIKefa2S-6yiHXrP7DMQ35RI8KKb7WlSdK8UoQ24SG8bE0D1uDi_yIhQmnHIzPLWDDmFJCIG_w=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2W-_M1j4Gzd2qedZmijC3C4dQ1v_QJeLen-PjohYn6rNjyhkK4HaGUgsScgRtqrDd6XSjjxcUWeyJ3-8-_sR42T5l8mXed_hTTiXwa3edMRpvZK9BAPmrbW6P81m0GcKtGDyFk=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass