hbdusIHn0QI9omOw9DWq6mNk_FsJnA0i=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0JRwVOFQo7sIxzNsIT0NPq-GO46G395nxGgHP1K_lYVjRFhHwfYx1QpU3SgS6V0MfYv-3sNagPmSJ6XIqP1as04_Sc-7zGDZUb_tnlSVDyiE9WIMYzlqjI-GItM-m8YCig63G7t3U7MoCX=k-no""],""When"":""2025-12-14""},{""Name"":""lion8584"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ7TY6tA9D5L4oIlUJD4IxZ2fz7QaaZi8ptijAViSQG81uRbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100"",""Rating"":4,""Description"":""First time having dined at this restaurant. For current and future viewers of this review, we visited during the [Christmas] holiday season; the decorations were absolutely amazing, elegant and semi-upscale, and made for a warm and friendly welcome. Plenty of parking, building is not a standard square/box; the outside was as pleasant as inside, ample seating, wait time was little to none (maybe two minutes and we were walk-ins with no reservations for a group of five). Staff were friendly and attentive. There were lots of birthday celebrations and the staff came out with a birthday dessert treat, playing drums and singing, very akin to the culture. Now to talk about the real reason for the review...the food! I snacked on chips and salsa waiting on my nachos and veggie flautas (I ordered more so I could take it home; definitely didn't eat all of this in one sitting!). The chips and salsa were sooo good! Incredibly good, fresh, baked chips and the salsa was freshly made, and not something from a can. There was a slight mix-up with the nachos, but it got corrected immediately after speaking with our server, so I don't view it as a negative, and only mentioning here since it was part of my overall experience. The taste was mouth-wateringly delicious. The Mexican cheese and the black beans enhanced the flavor, unlike any other place I've had nachos. Ingredients were fresh! I had a taste of the flautas after the nachos and while it tasted fine, they did not use Mexican cheese and it definitely effected the taste for me (I would not order them again). Nothing wrong with it, but I should've stuck with only the nachos. Everyone in my company enjoyed their meal: the BBQ wings, tilapia, chimichanga, chicken tacos, and beef tacos; all full of flavors dancing on your tongue. Drinks were also decent sizes. No one had any complaints about the taste, quality, or portion size of their meal. I will say, we were initially a little shocked by the prices, as they are a bit higher for comparable restaurants in the tristate area. But in all honesty, I would go back tomorrow for those nachos; yes, I know it'd be two days after I went, but they are that good!!! All in all, I would definitely recommend Amigos. Happy eating!"",""Images"":[""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn37l9Ta_RCjnEun_VLWfQm3q2LyZiFJAPgwpF7BumBVFQHsDgBML1ZQLX4k6l5W6MQKPsnB9IH1RLKwjEaeC9aA-nsyYMMW4XkxuoqSlKw9il_CMpuX6WjX3OviqQx_nJNMw1hl5lSN3ZD5=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1szRyzoP-E4a33CaKih_s98P-NE81TRFdsW2YEBYq4tRxsxnzIIxNNe2BsgYjl8cFfIxm19QnwPPb_65FOcorFyGVQ4TMyNnhp4VTw21Qyhq1KBDE_1OT-Y_Zfm1o7FMscMLyJgBQiM2f2=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2GULdkiZEMo7J0H_oRiTMjxLNt8ydCMtCREOD6gheBSP9SsXkOR5CFXbAdx-6mmJsTJudzJ5iSHtGKKceFRg54-XCeVP7Pw41DypMKnnSnPvVLF8rYKurfa-Uv38f6gOjiy4KWQsMsW7E-=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3kz-3JJ7ezf3bBjqVmFjky9rmzXydeaxvtt3rWzu90SnG4kgWm310WPtK5Ndv2GKhMex4P9nGBYZSLb4dABZMp1xEKSqkPtNlQOkLsnuC8_EuedxLRSJW_qvibQn94iXOopyXhTpHRvffx=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2ZNhLeZJrn5x5C17YWgy-a4OwTMoDY0JqveFKqv9-hxOzkh_Df6-uwMC1MXbGhX3mxKR7JDjpsUrWoZgmxStlLK_lAqxcnrvbGTjD8dIw-p8e1MY65H8616D7xC2mdjTEApUuVIqM3SOha=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0p0Nk4NsR0AbA5VvxKEChka37WBvfOljaXo2L_vFihvUWH0q8mhmBEz7ABfsW-5nozgl2qxRfvJtn2F4EPsGC9TJ-UT-b4Os7Ni6g8LatqjEYPBufCOGvw8rREVzIyLwh-zTOuWZ5icQha=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0NPAlSn6HF2wylNrmXVfsj3BRkTqlxJ_A