1-v-N4rGmN2zJXGcwAroMTdM2hZXtB_7xAifGvoK02MBn3tT_Q_eKPjQLia9vo=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0gwdZPN_bkJyvX3-oo8mRGdv1ssAKBZf0vxWdmj-O9t3YP6mMr9uHvGDROAoMhfA1f6k1E460Ofv6alLtuZjacP7XZKnZVEUG7pW3t1rZVulZh17RY06QnE66aVH56AVB4EdF2LUqX4aE=k-no""],""When"":""2026-2-12""},{""Name"":""Elisa Almengor"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLhb8f_UJ91Ua4QbeV2QThGL5cj-ztKWjE7mBNFEsqR1LTooA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100"",""Rating"":5,""Description"":""Ok so after deciding for a while (since they had the old name) that I’d try every type of banh mi on their menu I FINALLY completed my quest and honestly? Hands down?\nThis is one of the best Vietnamese restaurants in the laurel- Beltsville area.\nThe food was quick to come out, delicious, hot.\nIt had excellent service, even though it was busy they were very quick to take my order.\nIf you’re going to order something get the Banh mi special it comes in like a skillet with some bread on the side.\nOverall amazing restaurant I’m always glad to return."",""Images"":[""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0erjPrgw64EqiuDvj3OKPHXX2LERDbCKfV-Hj-AnbszACf-mDeVN63CEdklNovrhxd6-ohhrCWGM1XuuCp3Kiytm4INU4uXMIxpfcwjvsPHnYoBmuhZSA-eVSl30tgvtDJBahmig2a8ylG=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0wq0hj0j05iXZEF9VhYnFXmZZVeSufFVHHpQS4eouvcT9pOMGpUjHyFNdii4sJ3zurfYiCPR1NOetc_jzCRjHp43Qz4C6J-TzqM5SOKnetA38eBwsekxZM3tbxxno6a8Ui4I2L-G4GUvMO=k-no""],""When"":""2025-11-29""},{""Name"":""R K"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjiTtGFWvjqLn6atJQlTqigi1L3wwMzjKa4X78HsxyumstW81l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100"",""Rating"":5,""Description"":""This is where Lulu's Gourmet Vietnamese Cuisine used to be. I have never tried lulu's before so im not comparing, but I was very impressed by this new management.\n\nVN Chopstick review:\n\nStaff: I was really very impressed with the staff. They were attentive, kind, and prompt. It was a busy lunch time and they gave all their customer attention.\n\nFood: They had good options for fair price. Summer rolls and sauce was great, pho was great and thai tea was great.  The food was good temperature to eat, came out promptly and tasted great.\n\nIll definitely be back here."",""Images"":[""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0_P3OKyDsN3_jBfBAqr7WW0CR2dUWlmHHdxNt4BwZEs31BECiMdvRsYn8DDrRAyhNCehG3pt9ggbnobAQd4RxblMNr0m03DqrT6tSNS-8ObT4WXbpvNop0FBNF6pVuztnUdEsyXH_Wpw0=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2vi6dqvL3BF9bagDnfikNoTiEnzxLUzGcbkjt6UjDDSkVq2HbIMXkKLxeCcqewuZBZg8rWBiJ06a4rjMGr2jOtaL8BuPPRfXzmfjO1Y9v0BYm16KJ2uo03_aRVEFxn3DaPB5Em85bUQ59a=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1_H96lajQta2jLAFRLRewQYKUmXCX0bS_YIkTyB8LU_C7yP791OLX8Y6q4IGpUhgqirl5ouuNTP3Vf9Q603Pezepq9_2TEAfLO6mHw1becnn78Co5Uf9wXm643d0KAlIeSAD8F3H8eystL=k-no""],""When"":""2025-8-9""},{""Name"":""Char Z-P"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1RZYD8vjMoN5CPuDjG0Q7WXzi8QRg2hfMKKlElDi1QtfYXlo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100"",""Rating"":5,""Description"":""Can’t understand how this place isn’t talked about more, one of the best pho places in Maryland. I’ve come back with my friends like 5 times already because we can’t get enough! The pho is so rich and fills you up for hours after! I’ve recommended this place so many times already!"",""Images"":[""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn24KINk8-kRZfnG-99GOJ9uHKcOFDtjMqEPHUObeAnAHWN1_komHWMb5NgwFvJsQyLkp5iiaH34mRGhuAcJY6hPMW2qFo3Yt6BZhaR9z0RTjbd8-JVn4D6qFtCgb3KkahM1e-xdQBYPx7wz=k-no""],""When"":""2026-2-18""},{""Name"":""T.J."",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZyn8BMyebYMsZTdf1P-GzbktiZPAjtWehyHFhC5KbaxTi8pyfrw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100"",""Rating"":5,""Description"":""VN Chopstick in Laurel is a solid spot for authentic Vietnamese flavors without any pretension—perfect for a quick, satisfying meal.The grilled pork banh mi is a standout: the baguette is perfectly crusty on the outside and soft inside, stuffed with juicy, well-marinated grilled pork that's charred just right, balanced with crisp pickled carrots, daikon, fresh cilantro, and a generous smear of pate. It's flavorful, messy in the best way, and hits all the classic notes.The tenderloin pho is equally impressive—the broth is rich and aromatic with those deep star anise and cinnamon notes, and the beef tenderloin slices are incredibly tender and melt-in-your-mouth. Plenty of fresh herbs, bean sprouts, and lime on the side to customize.Service is friendly and fast, portions are generous, and prices are reasonable."",""Images"":null,""When"":""""},{""Name"":""Jennifer Konish"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRhy2YeiW0Apx_L3A-NcKvKdBCbIjH3khf2JxkTUf5TuLQTqE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100"",""Rating"":5,""Description"":""Wow! After driving by and checking out the reviews I had to stop by for lunch. They weren't lying. This is quite possibly the best restaurant pho I've had. The broth is so balanced and served with such tender and fresh tasting cuts of meat. We also tried a bahn mi which was incredible as well. You can tell that they pride themselves on using fresh ingredients. On impulse I decided to try the egg cream coffee on my way out. The coffee was so strong it sent me into outer space, but that's what I needed. This is my new favorite pho place and I can't wait to try more of the menu next time."",""Images"":null,""When"":""""},{""Name"":""Josue A"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUvW8eR09yB-y7DntCC6VjghUtabxNLa5GYsl-89x6vD4h7E-byxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100"",""Rating"":5,""Description"":""Super tasty pho and a friendly service. all the dishes i tried were good. The appetizer wings with fish sauce are unique but really delicious."",""Images"":null,""When"":""""},{""Name"":""Tasha Do"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOG8CxUaHFBJI4opCS5kG8o3NZUq2mmaUjS1q6Vs5NPTrbB1U=s120-c-rp-mo-br100"",""