 it was from a kitchen window with an unwelcoming attitude, which made me feel like an inconvenience rather than a paying customer who had been waiting nearly an hour.\n\nThe food itself is good, but the long wait time and poor customer service take away from the overall experience. Customer service and an organized pickup process are just as important as food quality. Unfortunately, the wait and interaction changed the entire experience for me."",""Images"":null,""When"":""""}]",null,
