nd the economy right now.\nFriendly place overall but you could definitely save your money going elsewhere."",""Images"":null,""When"":""""},{""Name"":""Abc Bcd"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQZH0lbw2ZHy2AigXCdIjpfhcjLZBO2m6zYoNbss0q-yGfO1vWCg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100"",""Rating"":1,""Description"":""It's been a long time since I visited this restaurant.  When it first opened, I liked the variety of food and service. It had baked ham and fresh pizza. Years later, menu changed to more Asian food I don't like. Seafood menu of shrimp and crabs showed stale food. Hibachi grill was about a B+. Ice cream bar changed to cheap dixiecups. They still have marshmallows you can dip in chocolate stream. Staff still provided good service. They only hire Asian staff. Service was average.  Waiters were delayed in getting you drinks you paid for. Restaurant had new furniture.  Restaurant was clean for a busy Sunday afternoon.  The price went up, but they offer senior discounts.  Overall impression was C+."",""Images"":null,""When"":""""}]",null,
