restaurants in the area, but Elsi will be our go to spot from now on. I truly appreciate the owners and server earning my business."",""Images"":null,""When"":""""},{""Name"":""Rajesh Prabhu"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLU4N3eHFMGeo_vNXvVxtwqpesMZBPR7Y5qZzyhHKGa1W2bZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100"",""Rating"":5,""Description"":""Great Ethiopian place and wonderful atmosphere. I was visiting Maryland and came across this place, drove right away and got my fav veg combo and chicken dish. The plate was really huge. The food tasted fantastic. Affordable price and great customer service. Will definitely visit again and it's a great place to try if you like authentic Ethiopian food. ❤️❤️❤️👍👍👍\n\nP.S. It would be great to reduce excess oil in the recipe and provide more vegetarian options"",""Images"":[""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1t0PrFOcntW7Q8sM6UIm_lReV5kEoVfNZMdcIBmOBCFmGbCSqkJypkv80q61d9O7WYaW6vNoksYzcFOdFoj6rUQzcxOElNogC3SdIhwXqabTfDiPB7_WEILHPivppWzmyvP7k=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3n-GbNOI8RdO6kjOnvx2wLNJ3OW8NSJ9l_vcmfjHGXqSvFYia02hB_wajI88TsNIsA8M-Rtf1HtRSxBG7KtDhyGpNCa9X8bro67hvWATCeY60YhhzEUYAGkxOi1J-Qu7z1bpd5=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn23XdzWtxmEA_9t-jySaIFc8qsn7R5uZ-5X80Nt6ejYjcG2S-OP3AIkwQor7fEmJGnKHZ6x52_5ARNS5HMlmbHPjSlrH-8lAQ_bsRqdQ84fAQHxVaOm2Bu0KjcwVF36vJSQK44=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2uZMIhj7nEsIuH9ZYF9XEs1vHudDIRPorKs5Os3dt42rShAgRSKeQPXm9Tc7P1DfLFfoY53pX01id99GoNrYNZenWeOGS2NUksdtvcY_jksQ5upNQb-Cyjx4oMFpkpQd8L4f3eLg=k-no"",""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1Xn-VbV4zYNArR246Wb2krOoH0CBk3hc6pYIi56w9c5Cjsilv8uiQFQHI2qqgUATIV6LrUWUo62nPd54u_E50svtAwGf-Yqug0IxYocY4fn0JTkgQgOuBtb33JTEHodvDVhTpFcw=k-no""],""When"":""2025-5-13""},{""Name"":""Yedidiya Habetamu"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhmq6FRJTl7S2sc852ZUOnfhpi9fUsQEAbuvKEGXB5BDvjVgM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100"",""Rating"":1,""Description"":""I don't even know what to really say for this restaurant. The place was really good and has a fancy look. The food wasn’t terrible, we tried the Veggie Combo, but it definitely didn’t justify the price. The biggest issue was the service — it was slow, inattentive, and overall disappointing. Unfortunately, I wouldn’t return.I was really disappointed with my experience. What made it worse was the poor service — it felt disorganized and inattentive. Then what really surprised me was the automatic 18% gratuity added to the bill. For the level of service we received, that felt unjustified."",""Images"":null,""When"":""""},{""Name"":""Neima Nasser"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK2I10O41_WFO83FOiGG8pB7DHaMoci_amHpYpVOv_IO_a_pg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100"",""Rating"":3,""Description"":""I took a few coworkers out for lunch, and the food was delicious. However, when the bill arrived, an 18% gratuity had already been included. After giving our card when the receipt came back for signature it still asked for an additional tip, which felt a bit ironic. I’m sure many people wouldn’t notice and might end up tipping twice, which was strange. Overall, the food was good, but the restaurant was a bit cold considering the winter weather."",""Images"":null,""When"":""""},{""Name"":""Solomon J"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIXlTbZ9e6X2GC46WvuuInQ2fnKbCFFwJFummzinGOV-cWm9A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100"",""Rating"":5,""Description"":""We ordered takeout Doro Wat in the medium-size aluminum foil tray, and it was amazing—truly tasted like back home. The flavor was authentic, and everyone in my family enjoyed it.\n\nThe only thing I want to be honest about for anyone reading this review is the price. Compared to other restaurants in the area, this same medium takeout tray can be about $20–$25 more. That said, the quality and authenticity of the Doro Wat we received were excellent, so for us it was worth it. I can’t fairly compare it to other Ethiopian restaurants nearby because I haven’t tried them yet.\n\nOverall, I would recommend this place—especially if you’re having a small gathering or a holiday party at home and don’t want to cook. Give them a chance—you won’t be disappointed."",""Images"":null,""When"":""""},{""Name"":""Adam Lenarz"",""ProfilePicture"":""https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJ8n3iHsZzEUOEnZ-jV-wm_IrojMx5-gkit7_r0THLVEWosG8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100"",""Rating"":1,""Description"":""Called ahead and reserved. No one greeted us for 5 minutes until we flagged someone down. Finally we ordered. Nothing came for 40 minutes, and when we asked they said another 20 minutes. 30 minutes after, we just left, no one even noticed. If this restaurant was downtown and had the best Ethiopian food in the world, maybe worth the poor service. Instead this is way out in the burbs."",""Images"":null,""When"":""""}]",null,
